data.title: Same as the Other Starbucks I Frequently Visit
data.text: Again, this Starbucks branch which I rarely visit only because I'm used with with the one in Naper Blvd., is still exceptional! They were able to provide me the one and only bag of Kopelani coffee which sold out in all the other stores including the one I frequent to!

data.title: Coffee was Great But Drive Through Acted like she did me a favor
data.text: Used the drive through window to order a coffee to go. The voice sounded friendly when ordering. When I got to the drive up window she handed me the coffee, I gave her my starbucks card, she gave it back to me and I handed her a $1 tip. No thanks you. How rude. Then she was annoyed I asked for my receipt.

data.title: Terrible Service More Often than Not
data.text: I go to this Starbucks on a daily basis, only because it is close to my office. More often than not, the service is terrible. The wait time for a cup of coffee is longer than any other Starbucks that I go to. When anything is ever mentioned to the employees, because of waiting over 5 minutes for a cup of coffee or a forgotten order, the response is more often than not unprofessional and in poor customer service taste.  I would suggest not going to this one if necessary.  There are so many Starbucks to typically chose from, I would definitely suggest passing this one by if you can.

data.title: Excellent Location
data.text: Had to stop in for a few hours and get some work done while on vacation. This Bux is very roomy, lots of space to spread out and work.  Staff was really nice and on top of their game behind the counter.  Crowd is a good mix of students and locals.  Nice and quiet overall.
